==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stell
<hw>Stell</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>stellan</ets>. ⟦root⟧163.]</ety> <def>To place or fix firmly or
permanently.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stell</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stell
<hw>Stell</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Stell</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A prop; a support, as for the feet in
standing or climbing.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A partial inclosure made by a wall or trees, to
serve as a shelter for sheep or cattle.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. &
Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stellary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Stellar</ent>⟦br⟧
